  "prompt": "Is 20 years old still young?",
  "response": "Yes, 20 years old is still considered young. At 20, individuals are typically in the early stages of adulthood, often pursuing higher education, starting their careers, or exploring their interests and independence. Many developmental psychologists consider the age range of 18 to 25 as \"emerging adulthood,\" a period characterized by significant personal growth and exploration. So, in many contexts, 20 is seen as a young age with plenty of opportunities for development and new experiences.",
